<p><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Since 2003, the U.S. Department of Labor&rsquo;s (USDOL) Office of Apprenticeship (OA) has focused on the health&shy;care industry to address both chronic workforce shortages and increasing skill demands for key occupations within the allied health and long-term care industries.</span></span></p><p><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Since then, apprenticeship programs have been developed in healthcare for 40 occupations, including four focused on Health Information Technology. These programs offer competency-based and time-based models, portable credentials and wage increases, responding to the needs for a high-skilled healthcare workforce.&nbsp;</span></span></p><p><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">And remember, under apprenticeship programs, you can earn while you learn sought-after healthcare skills &ndash; now that&rsquo;s a pretty good deal!</span></span><br />
<br />
<span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>How does this work? &nbsp; </strong></span></span></p><p><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><em>Using Registered Apprenticeship to Build and Fill Healthcare Career Paths </em>is a short, useful guide for understanding how apprenticeship training works, including highlights of ten model programs. It is published by the USDOL Employment and Training Administration, and is available on the Office of Apprenticeship on its website at: <a href="javascript:popit('http://www.doleta.gov/oa/pdf/Apprenticeship_Build_HealthCare_Paths.pdf')">http://www.doleta.gov/oa/pdf/Apprenticeship_Build_HealthCare_Paths.pdf</a></span></span><br />
<br />
<span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Where can I find out about healthcare apprenticeship opportunities in my State?</strong></span></span></p><p><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Information about healthcare apprenticeship opportunities can be obtained from several sources on the Office of Apprenticeship website at: <a href="javascript:popit('http://www.doleta.gov/oa/contactus.cfm')">http://www.doleta.gov/oa/contactus.cfm</a>. Use one of the following three links under &ldquo;Offices Contact Information:</span></span></p><ul><li><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Regional Office Contact Information &ndash; Find your State listed within one of the six USDOL Regions</span></span></li><li><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Office of Apprenticeship State Offices Contact Information &ndash; Contacts are listed for 43 States</span></span></li><li><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">State Agencies &ndash; Contacts are listed for the remaining 7 States, the District of Columbia, Puerto Rico, and Guam; in addition some of the 43 States on the above list are repeated here.</span></span></li></ul><p><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Where can I get some more information about apprenticeships? &nbsp; </strong></span></span></p><p><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The Office of Apprenticeship website provides more information about how to find an apprenticeship program in your area that may be of interest to you. This website is at: <a href="javascript:popit('http://www.doleta.gov/OA/')">http://www.doleta.gov/OA/</a><br />
<br />
